Name: UCSB
Description: A great university located along the California coast!

Name: Wakaliwood
Description: One of the most well-know movie production group based in Africa. Some of their most popular works are "Who Killed Captain Alex" and "Bad Black".

Name: Angkor Wat
Description: Covering 1.6 square kilometers, this massive Buddhist temple is a symbol for Cambodia.

Name: Stanley, Falkland Islands
Description: Stanley is the capital of the Falkland Islands, which the British and Argentinians faught for in 1982. Fun fact: there are 150 times more sheep than humans here!

Name: Lituya Bay
Description: Lithuya Bay is located in Southern Alaska. In 1958, a massive earthquake here triggered a mega-tsunami of more than 500 meters in height.

Name: Solheimasandur Plane Wreck
Description: In 1973, an American military plane crashed here in Southern Iceland, and it has since become a tourist attraction.
